2. Using stoichiometry, find amount of A that reacted with C in the titration.
3. Note: amount of A that reacted with C in the titration = amount of A that did not react with B earlier
4. Therefore, amount of A that reacted with B = total amount (known excess) of A added - amount of A that did not react with B earlier
