An organic synthesis generally involves carrying out a reaction to form the desired organic product with reasonable yield and purity. Various strategies are used in syntheses to obtain high yield and good purity of products. This usually involves careful sequencing of steps, controlled reaction conditions, complex set-up and/or equipment, and often, the investment of time. The product must also be isolated (i.e. separated from the reaction mixture) and purified.

