### Heterogeneous Catalysis

In heterogeneous catalysis, the catalyst and the reactants are in different physical phases.

* The catalyst is usually in the solid phase and it provides active sites at which the reaction can take place.
* The reactants are usually gases or liquids.

Example: Haber process (manufacturing of ammonia)

#### Mode of action of the catalyst

* Adsorption: Gaseous reactant molecules, N2 and H2, diffuse towards surface of the Fe catalyst. N2 and H2 adsorb onto the active sides of Fe catalyst by formation of weak attraction forces.
